'''Fcitx''' ('''F'''lexible '''C'''ontext-aware '''I'''nput '''T'''ool with e'''X'''tension) <nowiki>[ˈfaɪtɪks]</nowiki> is an input method framework with extension support.

== Installation ==
Install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx}}:
{{USEflag|package=app-i18n/fcitx
|cairo+yes+yes
|debug
|gtk++yes+Install GTK2 IM module
|gtk3+++Install GTK3 IM module
|introspection
|lua
|opencc
|pango+yes+yes
|qt4++yes
|snooper
|static-libs
|table+yes++Adds support for table-based IM systems like Wubi, Erbi
}}
{{Note|It is strongly recommended to add the ''gtk'', ''gtk3'' and ''qt4'' USE flags when you have applications using these toolkits.}}

{{Emerge|app-i18n/fcitx}}

== Using Fcitx ==
In order to use Fcitx in X, you need to add these environment variables (you need to export them after setting these variables):

If you use GDM, KDM or [[LightDM]] to login, add them to {{Path|~/.xprofile}}. If you use '''startx''', [[SLiM]], etc. to login, add them to {{Path|~/.xinitrc}}.
{{File|~/.xprofile or ~/.xinitrc||<pre>
XMODIFIERS="@im=fcitx"
QT_IM_MODULE=<module>
GTK_IM_MODULE=<module>
</pre>}}

If you installed with ''gtk'', ''gtk3'' or ''qt4'' USE flags ''<module>'' will be `fcitx', otherwise it should be `xim'.

It is recommended to start the [[D-Bus]] session bus before Fcitx starts. Add these to the '''beginning''' of your X startup file ({{Path|~/.xprofile}} or {{Path|~/.xinitrc}}):
{{File|~/.xprofile or ~/.xinitrc||<pre>
eval "$(dbus-launch --sh-syntax --exit-with-session)"
</pre>}}

{{Warning|If you want to use Fcitx in X, your [[Localization|locale]] '''cannot''' be ''C'' or ''POSIX''.}}

== Configuration ==
You can edit Fcitx's configuration file at {{Path|~/.config/fcitx/config}}.

Also, there are GUI tools to configure Fcitx. You can install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-configtool}} (based on gtk2 or gtk3) or {{Package|app-i18n/kcm-fcitx}} (based on kcm) to use them. (You may need to add the '~arch' keyword in {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} to install them).

== Frontend ==

Other than the built-in classic ui, there is also a frontend which integrates into KDE well, called Kimpanel.

It is included in {{Package|kde-base/kdeplasma-addons}}. And you must enable the dbus USE flag to use Kimpanel. Just add the kimpanel plasmoid to your plasma panel and fcitx will switch to it it self.

== Input Method ==

=== Chinese ===

Fcitx itself has built-in pinyin support. If you enable the table USE flag, you will have multiple table-based input methods, such as WuBi, Ziranma.

You can install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-cloudpinyin}} to have a better result in your candidate words list.

The built-in pinyin use a simple algorithm, and there are other pinyin input methods using other algorithms. You can install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-sunpinyin}}, {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-libpinyin}}, {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-rime}} to use.

For Bopomofo support, you can install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-chewing}} or {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-libpinyin}}.

For Cangjie, Boshiamy support, you can install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-table-extra}}.

=== Japanese ===

Install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-anthy}}.

=== Korean ===

Install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-hangul}}.

